               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra- 120rb)
 -
                     Introduction (fols.3ra-8vb)
 - Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols.
                     9ra-16rb)
 - Maṣḥaf za-wäḍʾat ʾǝm-ʾIyarusalem “Book that Came from
                     Jerusalem” (fols. 16rb-22va)
 - Antiphons (kǝśtat, ʾaryām, salām) (fols.
                     26vb-28va, 43rb-44rb, 48rb-48vb, 50rb-51va, 51va-52rb, 55rb, 57rb-58vb, 60rb,
                     61vb-62rb, 64vb-65ra, 68va-vb)
 - Homily by St Jacob of Sarug for the
                     funeral of priests and deacons (fols. 69va-72vb)
 - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā,
                     Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 86ra-91va)
 - Lǝfāfa ṣǝdq “Bandlet of
                     Righteousness” (fols. 91va-94vb)
 - Mangada samāy “Journey to Heaven”
                     (fols. 94vb-95vb)
 
 Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#1va">1va</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘተወልደ፡ መድኅን፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለማርያም፡ ከዲህ፡ ወስመ፡
                        ብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ አናንያ፡ ወአቡሁ፡ ወልደ፡ ሳሙኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወውሉዱ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ወወለቱ፡ ወለተ፡
                        ሥላሴ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ትንሣኤ፡ ወአኃዊሁ፡ ወልደ፡ አብርሃ፡ ገብረ፡ አናንያ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘተጽሕፈ፡ በዘመነ፡
                        ማቴዎስ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ በገበዘ፡ ክፍለ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ በ፲፻፡ በ፰፻፡ ፸ወ፯፡ አመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በወርኃ፡
                        የካቲት፡ ሠኑዩ፡ ሠርቀ፡ ሌሊት፡ ፲ወ፭፡ መዓልቱ። ዘተሣየጦ በንዋዩ ፲ወ፪ ብር። ዘሠረቆ ወዘፈሀቆ ውጉዘ ለይኩን በሥልጣነ
                        ጴጥሮስ ወጳውሎስ።<locus target="#1va">1va</locus>: This book is of Tawalda Madḫǝn
                        that he gave to Māryām Kädih. The name of his wife is Walatta ʾAnanǝya, his
                        father is Walda Sāmuʾel, his mother is Walatta Hāymānot, his son is Gabra
                        Māryām, his daughters are Walatta Śǝllāse, Walatta Māryām, Walatta Tǝnśāʾe and
                        his brothers are Walda Abraha, Gabra ʾAnanǝya, Kidāna Māryām. It was written in
                        the year of Mathew, during the reign of King Yoḥannǝs and (the time of) gabaz
                        Kǝfla Ḥawāryāt in 1877 year of mercy in the month of Yäkatit (= 22 February
                        1885 A.D.) … According to the note, the commissioner has paid 12 Birr to buy
                        the Ms. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
