                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the commissioner and his
                           family members; a few lines in the incipit page of the text, alternating
                           with black lines; two groups of lines alternating with black lines in
                           fol. 9r; two initial lines of each section of the text; names of Hebrew
                           letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 29vb, 33vb); elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., ṣällǝyu
                           (e.g., fols. 14ra, 15rb), nǝbäl kʷällǝnä (fols. 13va, 14rb), wäyǝbälu
                           ḥǝzb (e.g., fols. 17rb, 18ra), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 30rb, 31vb),
                           wa-tǝbl (e.g., fols. 32va, 33rb), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (fols. 36rb, 40ra).</seg>
